Popular Nigerian singer, Davido has said he would not want to be remembered just for his music. The singer who recently released his album ‘A better time’ said this on Sunday via his Twitter page. According to Davido, he would want to be remembered for giving Nigeria and Africa at large a good name. He would also want to be remembered for being a blessing and serving humanity. His tweet read: “I would want to be remembered for a lot, not just music to be honest. That I served for humanity, I served the people and a lot of people gained from my blessing. “I gave my family a good name, I gave my country a good name, I gave Africans a good name.”
